Well done, $(context.player.Name). I hope you're satisfied now. ::He yawns.::

::You see a frown on Vencel's face, and he speaks to you in a matching tone of voice.::

What was that all about? What did cameras ever do to you, $(context.player.Name)? I mean-- There was no reason to do that. Man...
Go through the gate, $(context.player.Name).

::An unexpected yawn interrupts Vencel. He instinctively raises his left hand to cover his mouth, forgetting that he is wearing a respirator. A tiny smile creeps up on your face due to this very fact, yet you understand that after so many hours of testing these kinds of lapses tend to sneak up on people.::

Hey, $(context.player.Name).

Excuse me. All in all, $(context.player.Name), as far as I'm concerned we're done here. I've got a few other things to do, but unless you'd like to have another go at the testing range, you have no reason to stay here any longer.

Anyway, are we finally done?

::His tired eyes aren't exactly radiating joy at your response, but he still nods.::
